Bancroft Convertible Fund said theU.S. District Court for the District of New Jersey issued apreliminary injunction, enjoining &lt;Zico Investment HoldingInc's> tender offer for Bancroft.    It said the Court order prevents Zico from buying anyshares tendered to them during the offer, which began on Feb.17, 1987.    In the tender offer blocked by the Court, Zico offered tobuy 500,000 shares, or about 22 pct of Bancroft's outstandingstock, for 30 dlrs a share.    Previously, Zico had bought 965,000 Bancroft shares for 31dlrs a share, giving it about 28 pct of the company. If therecent offer had gone through, the Zico would have ownedslightly more than 50 pct of Bancroft's outstanding shares.  Reuter&#3;